public interface IActivate

The methods provided by this interface are used to transform an object tree from an active into a passive representation and vice versa. Method names start with an _, because the actual implementations are usually generated by the idlc compiler.

Author:
Erwin Aitenbichler

_getExternalTypeName

java.lang.String _getExternalTypeName()
